author: ccripe@idahostatesman.com (Chadd Cripe)
title: Boise State football returns to Top 25
text:
Boise State football returns to Top 25 Posted by Chadd Cripe on October 4, 2015 2015-10-04T17:36:00Z Print 
The Boise State football team’s three straight blowouts impressed enough voters to get the Broncos back into the Top 25. 
Boise State is No. 24 in the Amway Coaches Poll and No. 25 in The Associated Press Top 25 released Sunday. The Broncos (4-1) had been absent from the previous three polls because of the loss to BYU. 
The Broncos have won their past three games by a total of 149 points, including two shutouts. 
Boise State is the highest-ranked Group of Five team in the Coaches Poll. Memphis of the American conference is No. 25. 
Toledo at No. 24 is the highest-ranked Group of Five team in AP. 
Boise State plays at Colorado State on Saturday.
